However I think you failed you recognize the heart of the argument. Saddam is not suicidal. And theres little evidence to support a link between his government and terrorist. In fact I imagine if one were to try, it wouldn't be difficult to make a stronger connection between our government and terrorist groups.<br>
<br>
Cheney and a few others within our government had been looking for a reason to reenter Iraq prior to Sept 11th. The terrorist attack just gave them the pretense of an excuse. And its kind of dismaying to see how effective that stratagy's become. Bush goes from Osama, Osama, Osama, to Saddam, Saddam, Saddam, and its as if a good portion of our population hasn't even noticed the switch.<br>
<br>
But I agree with Ebany, something has to be done. And its about time we wake up and realize that sending in the troops is not the best solution. I hate to use a cliche, but violence does beget violence, and this is certainly a case where that will hold true.<br>
